# CI/CD Pipeline Patterns

## Overview

Our CI/CD pipeline ensures reliable and consistent deployments through automated processes.

## Pipeline Stages

### 1. Build

- Code checkout
- Dependency installation
- Type checking
- Build process
- Asset optimization

### 2. Test

- Unit tests
- Integration tests
- E2E tests
- Coverage reports
- Performance tests

### 3. Quality

- Linting
- Code formatting
- Security scanning
- Dependency audits
- Bundle analysis

### 4. Deploy

- Environment selection
- Configuration management
- Deployment process
- Health checks
- Rollback preparation

## GitHub Actions Configuration

```yaml
name: CI/CD Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches: [main, develop]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main, develop]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
        with:
          node-version: '20'
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: npm ci
      - name: Type check
        run: npm run type-check
      - name: Build
        run: npm run build

  test:
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Run tests
        run: |
          npm run test:unit
          npm run test:integration
          npm run test:e2e

  quality:
    needs: build
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Lint
        run: npm run lint
      - name: Security scan
        run: npm audit

  deploy:
    needs: [test, quality]
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Deploy
        run: npm run deploy
```

